**Shape decision (locked HITL 2026-05-24):** OpenReport is exposed
as an **engine-attached accessor method** `engine.openReport()`
returning `OpenReport` (sync — the data is already in memory after
open). `Engine.open` keeps its 0.6.0 signature
(`Engine.open(...) -> Promise<Engine>`). Sibling semantics to
`engine.counters()` — `openReport()` is the open-time-state
snapshot. Per `dev/plans/0.6.1-implementation.md` § "Q-002
resolution (2026-05-24)".

