commit 01f6d79b9652279ddbb64d4c7c5e8a82692638df
Author: Corey Thompson <coreyt@gmail.com>
Date:   Sun May 24 15:15:33 2026 -0500

    feat(0.6.1): surface OpenReport via engine.openReport() napi-rs accessor
    
    Shape D (locked HITL 2026-05-24): mirrors the OPENREPORT-py slice on the
    TypeScript/napi-rs binding. The structured open report is exposed as an
    engine-attached accessor `engine.openReport()` — sync return, no Promise
    — because the data lives on the napi Engine struct after open.
    `Engine.open(path, options?)` keeps its 0.6.0 signature (resolves to
    just `Engine`); no return-shape regression. Sibling semantics to
    `engine.counters()`.
    
    napi-rs binding adds `#[napi(object)]` types for `OpenReport`,
    `MigrationStepReport`, `EmbedderIdentity`; the report is stashed on
    `Engine` at open time as `Arc<RustOpenReport>` and deep-converted to the
    napi-object shape on each accessor call. Idiomatic camelCase comes from
    napi-rs's snake_case-to-camelCase derivation; surface fields are
    `schemaVersionBefore`, `schemaVersionAfter`, `migrationSteps`,
    `embedderWarmupMs`, `queryBackend`, `defaultEmbedder`. TS-side
    `binding.ts` declares the native shape; `index.ts` exposes
    `Engine.openReport(): OpenReport` end-to-end.
    
    Closes 12-TX parity matrix § 1 row 2 fully (both bindings now ✅) —
    py landed in OPENREPORT-py (AC-068c); ts now binds AC-068d via
    `src/ts/tests/openreport.test.ts` (3 cases: spec-locked fields,
    idempotency, Engine.open Promise signature unchanged).
    `dev/interfaces/typescript.md` 0.6.0 caveat removed; spec line at L27-29
    rewritten to point at the accessor; `engine.openReport()` added to the
    Engine-attached instrumentation list.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>

